    "description": "MCX International Enterprises is actively seeking a talented and motivated Financial Analyst to join our dynamic team in Jabalpur. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout MCX International Enterprises:\nMCX International Enterprises is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n• Liaise with banks, regulators, and financial institutions\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Manage credit risk assessment and loan appraisal processes\n• Conduct due diligence for mergers, acquisitions, and investments\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in QuickBooks\n• Proficiency in Python for Finance\n• Proficiency in Ind AS\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n• Proficiency in VBA\n• Proficiency in Power BI\n• Proficiency in GST\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with MCX International Enterprises!",
